1
00:00:03,560 --> 00:00:05,160
I'm getting a ton of compliments on it.

2
00:00:05,720 --> 00:00:06,640
Sometimes I pull it off.

3
00:00:08,640 --> 00:00:09,640
Thanks.

4
00:00:10,480 --> 00:00:12,360
What’s that, a new outfit?
-No, not at all.

5
00:00:12,440 --> 00:00:14,320
I actually wore it on my last birthday.

6
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:16,360
Really? It looks brand new.
-Seriously?

7
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:18,880
Still, there's something charming about you.

8
00:00:20,080 --> 00:00:21,920
Hop hop hooray, I’m a year older.

9
00:00:22,000 --> 00:00:23,440
Yeah, right, just a little bit.

10
00:00:23,520 --> 00:00:25,680
But still, the outfit, something...

11
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:30,240
Well, I don’t always pull it off.

12
00:00:31,120 --> 00:00:32,520
Mom, happy birthday!
-Thanks.

13
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:34,000
Happy birthday!
-Thanks, sweeties.

14
00:00:34,080 --> 00:00:37,000
How old are you?
-Age is just for ID.

15
00:00:37,080 --> 00:00:38,520
Tell me, do I look like your mom?

16
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:39,680
Mom is...

17
00:00:40,960 --> 00:00:42,720
What’s that, your parents' new ringtone?
-Yeah.

18
00:00:43,440 --> 00:00:44,360
Hello, Mom, Shabbat shalom.

19
00:00:45,560 --> 00:00:46,720
On my way to the family dinner.

20
00:00:47,560 --> 00:00:49,960
Friday dinner and a birthday cake for Shani.

21
00:00:50,440 --> 00:00:52,560
She had it two days ago, yeah.

22
00:00:54,280 --> 00:00:55,480
Doesn’t matter.

23
00:00:55,560 --> 00:00:57,480
Less, let’s drop it for now.
-What less?

24
00:00:57,560 --> 00:00:59,000
Just drop it, Mom, drop it.

25
00:01:00,160 --> 00:01:01,520
More or less. Never mind.

26
00:01:02,240 --> 00:01:04,519
Mom, say hi to Dad! Hi to everyone there, okay?

27
00:01:04,959 --> 00:01:07,400
Mom, there’s a cop behind us! I’m not using a hands-free.

28
00:01:07,480 --> 00:01:08,480
Hang up the phone...

29
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:11,600
You with the bald head, please pull over.
-Look, look, he’s stopping us.

30
00:01:12,840 --> 00:01:14,560
This is what I need on my birthday, right?

31
00:01:14,880 --> 00:01:18,520
Good evening, routine check,
car registration and driver’s license, please.

32
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:19,960
Here you go.

33
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:22,600
Bi
and Shai's
brother.

34
00:01:22,680 --> 00:01:25,160
Sit tight, where are the car documents?
-Hold on, why are you rushing?

35
00:01:26,600 --> 00:01:27,680
Here you go.

36
00:01:29,080 --> 00:01:30,360
Great, now he saw us talking on the phone.

37
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:32,960
And because of your mom, we’re getting a 750 shekel ticket.

38
00:01:33,040 --> 00:01:34,520
He didn’t see the phone,

39
00:01:34,680 --> 00:01:36,520
He said it’s a routine check.
-Okay, okay.

40
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:38,200
Alright, quiet, quiet, he’s coming.

41
00:01:38,280 --> 00:01:41,120
According to the documents, the only driver
allowed to drive this car

42
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:43,600
is B. Rosen! I assume that’s not you.

43
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:46,960
No, that’s me, officer,

44
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:48,480
it’s just my work car

45
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:51,280
and I can also register
my husband to drive it.

46
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:54,280
Really, and did you register?
-No.

47
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:57,520
So you just drove the car
without a proper license.

48
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:59,520
No, wait, wait, wait, I didn’t know,

49
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:01,960
she was supposed to take care of that.
-Yeah, yeah, officer,

50
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,920
Look, I just, I prepared
all the documents at work

51
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:05,600
just forgot to ask for the signature,

52
00:02:05,680 --> 00:02:08,840
I just have my birthday today.
See, here’s my birthday cake?

53
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:10,360
That’s my birthday cake.

54
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:12,920
And I got confused with all the...

55
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:15,520
I promise I’ll sort it out on Sunday.

56
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:17,480
Where’s the cake from?
-I bought it from the supermarket.

57
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:18,440
Yeah.

58
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:20,080
Okay, switch places with each other

59
00:02:20,160 --> 00:02:22,440
and until she sorts out the work approval

60
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:24,120
you’re not driving the car, got it?
-Sure.

61
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,400
This time I'll let it slide
but only because it's your birthday.

62
00:02:28,480 --> 00:02:29,800
Thanks, really, thank you.

63
00:02:30,720 --> 00:02:32,840
And you, put in a little more effort for your wife.
-Yeah, yeah.

64
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:38,600
You don't buy a birthday cake at the supermarket.
-What?

65
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:43,600
Here, this is your wife's parents' bakery
they have an open eye,

66
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:45,560
I'll be with you, just go later.

67
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:48,440
She just complicates things for them every day.

68
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:49,960
What happened this time? Who's on the phone?

69
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:55,560
I called Shai to wish him Shabbat Shalom
and to make sure they’re not coming here by mistake,

70
00:02:55,920 --> 00:02:59,960
but he forgot to hang up
so I heard a cop pulled them over because of her.

71
00:03:00,640 --> 00:03:03,280
She promised him she'd sort out the licenses

72
00:03:03,360 --> 00:03:05,640
but she didn’t, so he drove without...

73
00:03:06,040 --> 00:03:07,160
He trusted her.

74
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:09,720
He still doesn’t get that you can’t trust her.

75
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:11,760
Just do me a favor and don’t tell them anything,

76
00:03:11,840 --> 00:03:13,920
so they don’t think I’m eavesdropping on their call.

77
00:03:14,600 --> 00:03:18,960
I don’t need to eavesdrop on my son’s phone
to know he’s quietly suffering.

78
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:21,080
Quiet.
-You think he means we should buy another cake now?

79
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:22,000
They’re talking.

80
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:23,000
I’m pretty sure they are.

81
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:24,840
At least it’s cheaper than a report.

82
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:29,360
Oops, I forgot to hang up the phone.
-What?

83
00:03:29,840 --> 00:03:32,840
Great, now your mom
heard the whole conversation with the cop.

84
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:35,680
Shai, what happened to you? What, you think
my mom’s bored out of her mind?

85
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:37,680
She has nothing to do but listen to our nonsense?

86
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,360
That’s exactly what suits her.

87
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:42,000
Now she’ll bring it up
and make a big deal out of it for a year.

88
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:44,640
Your mom never misses a chance
to get at me, please.

89
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,040
You’re really paranoid.

90
00:03:46,120 --> 00:03:48,480
I know my mom
and you have no idea how wrong you are.

91
00:03:49,920 --> 00:03:54,040
I’d be happy if our son
had a wife a little more...

92
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,240
A little more...

93
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:04,600
Look at me, look at me and...

94
00:04:13,880 --> 00:04:16,040
Shabbat Shalom.

95
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:17,240
Shabbat Shalom.

96
00:04:17,320 --> 00:04:19,600
Happy birthday.
-Thanks.

97
00:04:19,680 --> 00:04:21,640
Happy birthday, my beautiful.
-Thanks.

98
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:24,800
Shabbat Shalom.

99
00:04:25,440 --> 00:04:28,800
Look, wow, that looks great on you.
-Nice, right? It’s from silk.

100
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:31,680
Yeah, I know, Mom told me.
-Learn.

101
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:33,840
Thanks.
-No problem.

102
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:36,000
Happy birthday, but why were you so late?

103
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:38,120
Because a cop stopped us.

104
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:40,800
Turns out I was driving without the right license

105
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:42,600
because it’s Shai’s car and I’m not allowed to drive.

106
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:46,320
So did you get a ticket?
-No, no, he let us go,

107
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:48,280
he saw the birthday cake,
he felt sorry for us.

108
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:52,360
But he made us buy
a fancier birthday cake.

109
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:55,440
350 shekels for a cake.

110
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:58,800
Dairy?
-No, it’s parve, it’s supposed to be tasty.

111
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:00,560
Give it here, I’ll help put it in the kitchen.

112
00:05:01,120 --> 00:05:03,480
Shai, how are your parents?
-Fine, really fine.

113
00:05:03,560 --> 00:05:05,520
Fine, fine, now they have something to talk about

114
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:06,960
and mostly someone to talk about.

115
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:14,160
Because he’s disorganized
he needed a tidy wife,

116
00:05:14,720 --> 00:05:17,120
but she’s worse than him by a few numbers.

117
00:05:17,200 --> 00:05:20,920
I really don’t understand why we keep
the service if we don’t use it.

118
00:05:21,520 --> 00:05:27,120
The service has emotional value
that passes down through the family.

119
00:05:27,200 --> 00:05:29,280
Oh, Riki, come on, from generation to generation.

120
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:32,800
Your mom got it from her mother-in-law
who had nowhere to throw it away.

121
00:05:32,880 --> 00:05:35,280
And when she moved to assisted living five weeks ago

122
00:05:35,360 --> 00:05:36,360
she threw this at you.

123
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:39,880
It's porcelain that's worth something.

124
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:42,400
It's even more valuable if it's not used.

125
00:05:42,480 --> 00:05:45,800
Didn't you see that BBC series about antiques?

126
00:05:46,200 --> 00:05:49,480
It's worth a lot.
-A lot. Seriously, Ben,

127
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,840
it's just gathering dust and dirt.

128
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:53,960
I’d sell it to an old-timer,

129
00:05:54,320 --> 00:05:57,240
better yet, you should sell the dust to a dust dealer

130
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:58,720
to sell it to the Turks.

131
00:05:59,280 --> 00:06:01,480
You're just being a grump because you don't like to clean.

132
00:06:01,960 --> 00:06:04,800
Hey, Riki, if I were a service,

133
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:08,760
would you take care of me and pamper my
ears like them?

134
00:06:08,840 --> 00:06:12,560
If you were my ear,
you'd stop talking nonsense.

135
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:14,880
Ouch.
-What happened?

136
00:06:15,480 --> 00:06:16,560
Your finger got stuck.

137
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:21,200
Wait, wait, Riki, just like it went in,
it’ll come out, don’t worry.

138
00:06:21,280 --> 00:06:23,480
Pinchas, it’s not coming out.
-Show me, show me for a sec.

139
00:06:24,240 --> 00:06:26,280
You need to apply soap, it’ll come out easily.

140
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:28,920
Go get soap from the bathroom.
-Okay, what kind of soap?

141
00:06:29,280 --> 00:06:32,440
What kind of soap? Brain-washing soap,
what does it matter?

142
00:06:32,520 --> 00:06:34,560
Just bring something.
-Alright, alright, I’m on it.

143
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,520
Maybe conditioner?
-Go, just go already.

144
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,600
Alright, come on, it’s late, to the table.

145
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:47,080
Wait, wait, I made the salad today.

146
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:50,320
Too bad you told them how much the cake cost

147
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,760
because now no one cares about the food,

148
00:06:51,840 --> 00:06:53,680
everyone wants to know how she is.
-She’s really tasty.

149
00:06:53,760 --> 00:06:55,160
What?
-Did you open it?

150
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:57,240
Come on, couldn’t you wait? That’s my birthday cake.

151
00:06:57,320 --> 00:06:59,160
Pay attention to the second one, what happened?

152
00:06:59,240 --> 00:07:00,800
I want some too, Mom.
-After the meal.

153
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:02,080
But it’s not parve, Rachel.

154
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:03,120
Hey, did you see what they did to you?

155
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:04,760
Alright. Come on, Sali, kiddush.

156
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:07,760
"On the sixth day

157
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:10,360
the heavens and the earth and all their hosts were finished.

158
00:07:11,280 --> 00:07:13,240
And God finished on the seventh day..."

159
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,320
I’m sorry.

160
00:07:14,400 --> 00:07:16,120
That’s the scariest kiddush I’ve ever been to.

161
00:07:17,200 --> 00:07:18,640
It’s my parents, maybe something happened.

162
00:07:18,720 --> 00:07:20,040
Okay, call them after kiddush.

163
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:22,760
"...for in it He rested from all His work

164
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:25,200
which God created to do."

165
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:26,120
Ben, answer already.

166
00:07:26,200 --> 00:07:27,520
"Sabri Maranan."

167
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,480
Hello?
-Cheers.

168
00:07:29,040 --> 00:07:30,880
Shai, it’s Dad.
-Yeah, I know, Dad,

169
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:31,840
the shark told me.

170
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:33,160
What happened, is everything okay?

171
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:36,920
Almost okay. Mom got stuck in the service.
-What?

172
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,280
Her finger got stuck in the service.

173
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,760
How does a finger get stuck in the service?

174
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:42,200
In the ear of the service cup, hey.

175
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:45,920
No, how did that happen?
-It was an accident, don’t ask too many questions.

176
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:48,320
She’s hysterical, Shai, come as fast as you can.

177
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:51,000
But we’re in the middle of kiddush
and it’s exactly Shani’s birthday.

178
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:52,200
Amen.

179
00:07:53,200 --> 00:07:54,400
Alright, wait, Dad, I’m coming.

180
00:07:55,640 --> 00:07:57,680
I made the salad.
-Amazing.

181
00:07:57,760 --> 00:07:59,720
Did you cut it and season it?

182
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,840
Come here for a sec.
-What, is everything okay?

183
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:02,800
Come here for a sec.

184
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,080
What?

185
00:08:05,160 --> 00:08:06,000
Come on, what happened?

186
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:08,640
My mom got her finger stuck in the serving dish,

187
00:08:08,720 --> 00:08:10,200
Don't ask me how.
-No way.

188
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:12,880
Yeah, so she wants
me to come help her get it out now.

189
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:15,000
What, are you serious? What are you gonna do now?

190
00:08:15,080 --> 00:08:17,440
I’ll pop over to my mom’s,
help her get it out, and I’ll be back in half an hour.

191
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:19,160
Alright, come on, what should I do?

192
00:08:19,240 --> 00:08:21,680
Go, do it quickly and come back,
I want you here for the candle lighting.

193
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:23,120
Okay, babe, everything will be fine.

194
00:08:23,200 --> 00:08:26,120
What happened?
-Just a little mess with my mom,

195
00:08:26,200 --> 00:08:29,880
I need to go help
try to get a finger out of a serving dish.

196
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:33,280
Alright, come on, go fast and come back quick.

197
00:08:33,360 --> 00:08:34,240
Come on
-Come on, with pleasure

198
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:38,159
A lot of weird things happen to that woman, right?

199
00:08:39,799 --> 00:08:41,720
Did her finger turn blue or is it just me?

200
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:42,640
I’m dying.

201
00:08:42,720 --> 00:08:44,240
This is neither the time nor the place to die.

202
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:46,000
Don’t touch, please don’t touch.

203
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:49,560
Come on, Mom, it’s just a little twist of the finger
and it’ll be out.

204
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:55,640
Sometimes it gets stuck, the finger,
and then they have to take it off, right?

205
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:57,440
Come on, Mom, enough, you’re just stressing yourself out now.

206
00:08:57,760 --> 00:09:01,480
And then sometimes it gets complicated
and they have to disconnect the whole hand, right?

207
00:09:01,560 --> 00:09:04,560
How am I gonna manage without a hand?
-Trumpledor managed just fine.

208
00:09:04,640 --> 00:09:07,760
Mom, relax,
we’ll make sure nothing happens to you.

209
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:10,520
I can teach you how to disconnect your mind and thoughts.

210
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:14,360
Have you ever been to a course like that that calms you down?

211
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:18,840
Have you tried Vaseline?
-Why don’t you just break the cup?

212
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:19,840
Seriously, are you normal?

213
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:21,520
That’s part of the serving dish.
-No one touches the serving dish.

214
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:24,520
Absolutely not.
-Okay...

215
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:27,640
It’s a serving dish that’s been in the family.
-Alright.

216
00:09:27,960 --> 00:09:29,520
You’re right because if you break the cup,

217
00:09:29,600 --> 00:09:32,360
you could get hurt from the shards
which is way more dangerous.

218
00:09:32,440 --> 00:09:33,880
Okay, enough, enough, enough, I’m tired of these dramas,

219
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:36,440
I’m calling an ambulance,
they probably know how to handle this.

220
00:09:36,520 --> 00:09:39,480
No, I don’t want an ambulance, why isn’t Shai here?

221
00:09:39,560 --> 00:09:42,880
Why Shai, Mom? I’m here.
-I’m here too.

222
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:46,280
Why isn’t Shai here?

223
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:53,440
I’m sorry, babe,
I would’ve driven myself but I’m not allowed to drive.

224
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:54,640
If that cop stops us again,

225
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:56,560
even the cake from the best bakery in town

226
00:09:56,640 --> 00:09:57,680
won’t save us from embarrassment.

227
00:09:58,160 --> 00:10:00,640
Okay, it’s also my fault,
I didn’t organize the documents.

228
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:02,560
It’s fine, it’s okay, just make sure to come back quickly.

229
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:05,320
Just drive carefully so they don’t stop us again.

230
00:10:07,040 --> 00:10:08,840
Come on, just do it already,
I can’t stand this.

231
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:11,440
Come on, what’s going on, Shai?

232
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:13,560
We’re almost there, Dad.
-Okay.

233
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:14,720
What’s the rush?

234
00:10:15,280 --> 00:10:16,120
He’s coming.

235
00:10:17,160 --> 00:10:20,320
Maybe we should put ice on it
to reduce the swelling,

236
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:21,640
like we used to do for dogs.

237
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:24,480
Since when do dogs get stuck in serving dishes?

238
00:10:24,560 --> 00:10:26,480
Stop making fun of me.

239
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,400
Mom, lighten up, what’s the matter?

240
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,640
The kids aren’t here.

241
00:10:29,720 --> 00:10:31,560
Yeah, it's great, humor, it’s also calming.

242
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:33,400
They taught us that in this course too.

243
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:35,440
It’s messing with my head.
-Yeah.

244
00:10:35,920 --> 00:10:39,440
Did they teach you how to connect it there?
-I don’t remember.

245
00:10:39,520 --> 00:10:42,720
Look, I didn’t find ice
but I brought some frozen schnitzels.

246
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:45,000
What did you do? Did you take it out of the freezer?

247
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:46,480
Do you know how hard I worked on this?

248
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:49,800
It’s going to spoil, it’s food, put it back in the freezer.

249
00:10:49,880 --> 00:10:52,480
Riki, you need to be more relaxed.

250
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:54,800
I think I hear the ambulance downstairs.

251
00:10:55,280 --> 00:11:00,800
Pinchas, don’t let them take me away,
I want to die in my bed, at home.

252
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,440
Honestly, when I think about it

253
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:05,080
I’ve never heard of anyone dying
from a finger stuck in the service.

254
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:08,280
And waiting for many more weeks of suffering together.

255
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:11,720
They’re here, Mom, think about the suffering, it’s more calming.

256
00:11:11,800 --> 00:11:13,280
They definitely didn’t teach us that in the course.

257
00:11:14,720 --> 00:11:15,560
Please.

258
00:11:15,640 --> 00:11:17,680
You guys got here really fast, nice job.

259
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:19,360
I don’t need an ambulance.

260
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:21,800
Are you the guy?
-I’m the paramedic.

261
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:22,760
Oh.

262
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:25,920
What happened?
-Her what’s-it-called got stuck in the service.

263
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:27,320
Show me your finger.

264
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:37,880
I’ve been in the field for weeks and I have to admit
I’ve never seen anything like this.

265
00:11:39,040 --> 00:11:40,280
How did this happen to you?
-If you lived here,

266
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:42,440
you’d see a lot more things you haven’t seen yet.

267
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:45,720
Once Adam dated an Ethiopian girl.
-What’s that got to do with anything?

268
00:11:46,400 --> 00:11:47,800
You didn’t date her, Mom scared her away.

269
00:11:48,640 --> 00:11:53,000
Okay, fine, there’s really no problem here,
we just need to break the cup and that’s it.

270
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:56,160
No way, not in the middle of the service!

271
00:11:56,640 --> 00:12:00,040
I understand, ma’am,
but besides breaking it, there’s no other way.

272
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:01,480
And he doesn’t want to waste time,

273
00:12:01,560 --> 00:12:03,640
there are more urgent events than saving lives.

274
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:04,560
I’m dying.

275
00:12:04,640 --> 00:12:07,800
Wait, wait, so what do you suggest, bro?

276
00:12:07,880 --> 00:12:10,400
Listen, you need to calm her down,

277
00:12:11,480 --> 00:12:13,560
when her blood pressure is high, her finger swells up

278
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:16,800
and it never comes out. Just calm her down.

279
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:23,480
It’s okay, I’ll stay here at home
and I’ll calm myself down with the service.

280
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:27,120
The paramedic did his part, the paramedic can go.

281
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:33,440
Listen, when she’s calm
you need to scare her with something!

282
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:38,040
Then the blood comes out of the finger and the finger out of the service, got it?

283
00:12:38,440 --> 00:12:39,360
Yeah.

284
00:12:40,840 --> 00:12:43,240
So, who’s Itamar that called
to order the ambulance?

285
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:44,160
Me, me.

286
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:48,480
This is the ambulance charge, come pay soon.

287
00:12:48,560 --> 00:12:49,880
What to pay?

288
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:51,360
Isn’t it covered by the basket?

289
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:55,800
You’re kidding me, there’s barely any Tylenol and a band-aid in the basket.

290
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:57,120
If I don’t transport, it costs.

291
00:12:57,200 --> 00:13:02,480
Riki, I suggest you move to the living room
and there you can examine in peace.

292
00:13:02,800 --> 00:13:05,280
Great, now you want to kill me, Pinchas.

293
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:07,040
What? No way, Riki, no way!

294
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:10,320
But he said you need to relax
so come on, examine in the living room.

295
00:13:10,400 --> 00:13:14,480
And besides, Riki, don’t worry,
no one is going to kill you. Come on.

296
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,240
Wait, wait,

297
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:18,720
so maybe we should transport her after all,
are you sure not?

298
00:13:18,800 --> 00:13:20,920
Because she has a lot of issues.
-For sure.

299
00:13:24,760 --> 00:13:25,600
Hello.

300
00:13:26,560 --> 00:13:28,840
Is the ambulance for here?
-Yeah, relax, Shai.

301
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:32,160
But is everything okay?
-Yeah, yeah, we just need to calm her down and everything will be fine.

302
00:13:32,240 --> 00:13:34,080
Mom, are you okay? Do you want us to take you somewhere?

303
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:37,080
Turns out she doesn't need to go anywhere.
-We already know what to do.

304
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:40,600
Alright, the paramedic explained it to Ben more or less.

305
00:13:40,680 --> 00:13:42,360
Guys, see you later and good luck.

306
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:45,200
Thank you so much.
-Thanks, thanks, bro. Bye.

307
00:13:46,840 --> 00:13:51,360
Did you see that barbarian with the yogurt?
Breaking it, no respect at all.

308
00:13:51,440 --> 00:13:52,800
Why not break it, really?
-Are you crazy?

309
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:55,720
What, are you normal?
-It's the service. We don't talk about breaking anymore,

310
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:58,120
It annoys Riki, she needs to chill.

311
00:13:58,200 --> 00:14:01,120
Pinchas, it's been cooking a bit longer, notice that?

312
00:14:01,440 --> 00:14:03,400
Shai, Itamar, come to the kitchen for a sec.

313
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:06,480
Riki, maybe you should watch TV,
maybe that will calm you down?

314
00:14:07,040 --> 00:14:09,960
Riki, maybe I’ll read you the newspaper,
maybe that will calm you down?

315
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:12,200
Come on, have you lost it? You live in Israel, right?

316
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:14,920
Since when does a newspaper or TV
calm anyone in this country?

317
00:14:15,560 --> 00:14:18,120
Riki, only if Adam marries
someone from the alliance will that calm her down.

318
00:14:19,040 --> 00:14:20,160
That's true.

319
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:24,320
Listen, let’s do what the paramedic said.

320
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:27,200
Sit together in the ambulance.
-What did he say?

321
00:14:27,280 --> 00:14:28,480
Itamar.

322
00:14:28,560 --> 00:14:31,840
After she's calm, we need to
surprise her, scare her a bit.

323
00:14:31,920 --> 00:14:36,880
And then from the scare, the blood will come out of her finger,
we’ll pull it out and the finger will come off.

324
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:40,320
No, this whole scare idea
really doesn’t sound logical to me.

325
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:43,120
What, do you think the blood sits in the finger,
we come, scare them

326
00:14:43,840 --> 00:14:44,960
and it moves to the second finger?

327
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:46,320
That's what the paramedic said.

328
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:49,760
Alright, Ben, let’s scare her,

329
00:14:49,840 --> 00:14:51,520
but not too much, so she doesn't have a heart attack.

330
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:53,080
Then they’ll have to take her away.

331
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:57,800
So, in short, does anyone have an idea on how to scare her?

332
00:14:58,360 --> 00:14:59,320
I have one...

333
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:02,840
)(9
And move,
,ְֲ ni

334
00:15:05,200 --> 00:15:08,240
Is there a story that makes it
impossible to break this cup?

335
00:15:08,320 --> 00:15:09,520
The set will be ruined.

336
00:15:10,680 --> 00:15:13,240
So break the plate
of the cup too, then no one will know.

337
00:15:14,040 --> 00:15:17,520
And then it’ll be five? Who's heard of a set of five?

338
00:15:18,080 --> 00:15:19,720
Who's heard of an odd set?

339
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:22,800
So maybe break another cup and another plate

340
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:25,840
and then four, a set of four exists, right?

341
00:15:25,920 --> 00:15:29,480
Can we stop talking about the set?
It's stressing Riki out and she needs to relax.

342
00:15:29,560 --> 00:15:32,760
I'm talking without pressure. On the contrary,
I actually think I'm calming her down.

343
00:15:32,840 --> 00:15:36,720
How can I relax
when my son almost got stopped because of you?

344
00:15:38,040 --> 00:15:40,280
I had a feeling this topic would come up.

345
00:15:40,840 --> 00:15:44,280
Well, my parents are waiting for me at home
with a cake that costs 350 shekels.

346
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:46,960
Congratulations, babe.
-Thanks, that was two days ago.

347
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:48,600
How lucky you are-
-What do you mean lucky?

348
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:51,440
Her birthday is on the ninth of Av.

349
00:15:51,760 --> 00:15:53,400
She looks calm and is going off.

350
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:56,480
Mom, don’t ask what happened.
-What happened?

351
00:15:56,560 --> 00:15:59,640
The freezer broke and all the schnitzels thawed,
everything needs to be thrown away.

352
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:00,640
No way.

353
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:02,680
What are you doing?

354
00:16:03,880 --> 00:16:06,000
Stop, this isn't working.
-What about the schnitzels?

355
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:07,400
Chill already with the schnitzels,

356
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:09,160
we just said that to scare Mom.

357
00:16:10,520 --> 00:16:11,400
Hello.

358
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:13,640
Are you guys completely out of your minds?

359
00:16:15,040 --> 00:16:16,360
The service almost broke.

360
00:16:18,680 --> 00:16:20,280
Yeah, Mom, we're still here.

361
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:24,040
Listen, sweetie, we just finished eating,
we're waiting to bring out the coffee and cake.

362
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:27,440
The kids and Moshe are going crazy.

363
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:30,840
When do you think you'll arrive?
-I have no idea, I don't know, come on,

364
00:16:30,920 --> 00:16:34,000
Riki got her finger stuck
in some cup, you know what?

365
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:35,360
An ambulance was here, it's gone.

366
00:16:35,440 --> 00:16:36,920
Alright, come do this as quickly as you can.

367
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:39,720
Because we can't handle the kids and Moshe anymore,

368
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:41,280
They're really glued to the cake.

369
00:16:41,360 --> 00:16:42,320
Is that her?

370
00:16:42,400 --> 00:16:44,320
Tell her I'm not waiting for her with the cake either.

371
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:45,600
Get here.

372
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:48,240
I don't know if you know

373
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:51,760
but the salad...
-you made it.

374
00:16:55,480 --> 00:16:56,480
So here's the thing,

375
00:16:58,400 --> 00:17:02,240
I've been trying to get pregnant for half a year,

376
00:17:03,720 --> 00:17:06,280
and we finally found out I have a problem with...

377
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:09,640
Ben, you came mixing up my poles.

378
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:12,760
Anyway, we used a sperm donor

379
00:17:13,760 --> 00:17:16,319
and Shani and I are going to have triplets.

380
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:18,200
I'm dying.

381
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:21,240
Just yesterday we found out they made a mistake

382
00:17:21,720 --> 00:17:24,359
and the donor is Ethiopian.
-What?

383
00:17:24,440 --> 00:17:25,400
What?

384
00:17:26,160 --> 00:17:27,119
Despite the color differences,

385
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:30,200
we decided to continue with the pregnancy.
-What?

386
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:34,160
Itamar, pull already, Ben, pull.

387
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:35,280
Give it to me, give it to me...

388
00:17:36,880 --> 00:17:37,880
What are you doing?

389
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:40,640
Just kidding, Mom, we wanted to scare you
into thinking your blood was coming out of your finger.

390
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:42,600
You guys are not normal.

391
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:47,840
You think you're going to scare me
with an Afro-Israeli triplet?

392
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:52,160
That'll be material to tease you about for the rest of my life.

393
00:17:52,640 --> 00:17:54,440
And you, what are you doing?

394
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:56,320
Why?

395
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:57,640
Honey, come to the bedroom for a second.

396
00:17:57,720 --> 00:17:59,920
I love the sound it makes,

397
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:05,440
it reminds me of the sound I used to make
when I’d hit you on the butt when you were little.

398
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,240
Why?

399
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:08,920
What's wrong with you?
-I want to tell you something.

400
00:18:09,680 --> 00:18:11,880
Listen to me carefully, with all due respect
to your mom and her finger,

401
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:14,040
my parents are waiting for us at home
and the kids are driving them crazy.

402
00:18:14,120 --> 00:18:16,640
You guys are messing around with all kinds of
silly scare tactics that aren't working.

403
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:19,360
Okay, we're just trying
to draw the blood from her finger,

404
00:18:19,440 --> 00:18:20,320
that's what the paramedic said.

405
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,240
So listen well, my blood is rising to my head too

406
00:18:22,320 --> 00:18:23,960
!and soon it's going to look for a way out.

407
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:25,640
The paramedic didn't tell you that, did he?

408
00:18:25,720 --> 00:18:27,240
Okay, honey, honey, I get you,

409
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:29,360
but I can't leave her like this,

410
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:31,320
we need to scare her and we're not succeeding.

411
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:34,160
Do you at least have a good scare idea?

412
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:36,640
Yeah, I have a great idea.

413
00:18:37,120 --> 00:18:39,120
Alright, I...

414
00:18:39,800 --> 00:18:41,840
It hurts so much.

415
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:43,400
I'll stay a little longer.

416
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:44,600
Riki, you won't believe what happened.

417
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:47,160
Now, why in the middle?

418
00:18:47,720 --> 00:18:48,640
I'm on the balcony.

419
00:18:48,720 --> 00:18:50,920
What is this? Another scare attempt?

420
00:18:51,960 --> 00:18:53,080
This is for Shani.

421
00:18:53,960 --> 00:18:55,280
It's not the same sound.

422
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:02,480
Yeah, we're still here.
-What's up, babe?

423
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:05,120
Manny and Alin are leaving because of the baby.

424
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:08,880
What about the little ones?
-Visiting with Dad.

425
00:19:09,520 --> 00:19:11,600
What about Shai's mom?
-She's putting on a show here.

426
00:19:11,680 --> 00:19:13,920
Did you buy a ticket?
-Okay, enough, I'm done,

427
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:15,120
I'm going home.

428
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,160
I'm hungry.

429
00:19:18,520 --> 00:19:21,440
First time there's really nothing.
-What do you mean, nothing?

430
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:23,600
There is, I just can't do it like this.

431
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:25,680
Come on, I'll defrost some shlikler for you-

432
00:19:26,400 --> 00:19:27,760
Come on, Michal.

433
00:19:32,680 --> 00:19:33,560
Come.
-But food.

434
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:34,720
Now, now, come.

435
00:19:34,800 --> 00:19:36,440
But...
-I don't care, I don't care,

436
00:19:36,520 --> 00:19:38,200
It was supposed to be quick
and turned into a big mess.

437
00:19:38,280 --> 00:19:41,000
Fine, can I go after?
-We're moving now, do you hear me?

438
00:19:45,920 --> 00:19:48,360
Can we add some salt to this?
-After I'm gone.

439
00:19:48,760 --> 00:19:51,200
Okay, Mom, I see you're here with everyone,

440
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:53,200
so we're moving out.

441
00:19:53,280 --> 00:19:55,360
The finger is already cold, can you feel it?

442
00:19:55,440 --> 00:19:56,480
Sit down.
-No, no.

443
00:19:56,560 --> 00:19:57,400
Okay, we're moving.

444
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,000
It hurts so much.

445
00:20:00,760 --> 00:20:02,960
Riki, enough with that, okay?
-Enough with what?

446
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:04,200
Riki, enough, it's my birthday

447
00:20:04,280 --> 00:20:07,080
and my parents and my siblings
and my kids are all waiting to celebrate with me

448
00:20:07,440 --> 00:20:09,600
and here, not a single person
said happy birthday to me except Michal.

449
00:20:10,120 --> 00:20:15,320
If you think I forgot
your birthday, you're wrong,

450
00:20:15,880 --> 00:20:20,680
I planned to celebrate it
properly at our place on Saturday.

451
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:23,680
Yeah, Riki? How old am I, Riki?

452
00:20:25,560 --> 00:20:26,840
Confused person

453
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:31,120
remembers the birthday date but forgets the age.

454
00:20:32,320 --> 00:20:33,280
That's such an incorrect statement.

455
00:20:33,840 --> 00:20:35,240
Besides, I also have a gift for you.

456
00:20:35,320 --> 00:20:37,280
Really?
-Pinchas, shut up.

457
00:20:37,360 --> 00:20:39,480
Really?
-Yeah, why are you surprised?

458
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:42,160
What do you mean, a gift? Like wrapped and everything?

459
00:20:42,720 --> 00:20:46,160
No, not like that.
-Oh, then what kind?

460
00:20:48,360 --> 00:20:52,040
Since I don't have daughters of my own,

461
00:20:52,840 --> 00:20:57,440
I decided to pass this precious service to you

462
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,360
as an inheritance while I'm still alive.

463
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:02,120
Wow.

464
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:06,720
You're giving me the service, Riki?
-Yeah, sit down,

465
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:08,520
it’s passed down in our family from generation to generation,

466
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:11,240
Pinchas, shut up, it goes from my generation to hers.

467
00:21:12,080 --> 00:21:14,120
So Riki, does that mean...

468
00:21:15,080 --> 00:21:17,320
that this service is now mine?

469
00:21:19,200 --> 00:21:20,280
Yes.

470
00:21:20,360 --> 00:21:21,600
How lovely.

471
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:22,600
Thank you.

472
00:21:24,960 --> 00:21:26,080
The service.

473
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:27,360
The finger.

474
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:36,160
Say thank you that they left the cake from the store.

475
00:21:37,480 --> 00:21:39,080
Not even a bite from the second cake.

476
00:21:39,160 --> 00:21:42,040
Okay, Meirav and Moshe apologized, right?
-Yeah.

477
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:46,280
I'm a bit sad the girls didn't see
that they lit candles for their mom's birthday.

478
00:21:46,360 --> 00:21:47,760
Come on, babe,

479
00:21:48,320 --> 00:21:50,280
they'll have many more weeks with her.
-Yeah.

480
00:21:52,040 --> 00:21:53,760
What do you think, should we celebrate at your mom's tomorrow?

481
00:21:55,320 --> 00:21:57,480
I think we’ve had enough of your
birthday celebrations today.

482
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:05,600
Never mind, just leave the cake,
we’ll light the candles tomorrow morning at breakfast.

483
00:22:08,560 --> 00:22:09,520
It’s not important.

484
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,440
What happened?

485
00:22:15,320 --> 00:22:16,160
From the beginning.

486
00:22:16,240 --> 00:22:18,080
It’s my parents, something might have happened.

487
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:27,040
Where to?
-Where are you going?

488
00:22:29,040 --> 00:22:30,360
He’s going back to the dressing room.
-No!

489
00:22:32,240 --> 00:22:34,680
Alright, enough, I can’t take it anymore, folks,
I’m calling an ambulance.

490
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:36,040
They probably know how to handle this.

491
00:22:36,840 --> 00:22:40,080
I can’t, she’s killing me.

492
00:22:43,920 --> 00:22:45,000
Enough, Polly.

493
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:47,960
How can anyone stand this?

494
00:22:51,560 --> 00:22:52,800
This is for Shai.

495
00:22:55,600 --> 00:22:58,240
I’ll give them. Pinchas, be quiet.

